definition: abbr. for Afghanistan 阿富汗[A1 fu4 han4]
prefix used before monosyllabic names, kinship terms etc to indicate familiarity/used in transliteration/also pr. [a4]

sentences.english: Phet reached its greatest intensity off the coast of Oman on June 3.
sentences.chinese: 6月3日，“鑽石”在阿曼沿海達到最大強度。

sentences.english: The Omani people have all along held profound feelings towards the Chinese people.
sentences.chinese: 阿曼人民對中國人民一向有着深情厚誼。

sentences.english: The obvious place to start is Muscat.
sentences.chinese: 很顯然，馬斯喀特應該是遊歷阿曼開始的地方。

sentences.english: Critics said that Amanda is the sex symbol of the hard-bodied athletic world.
sentences.chinese: 批評者說，阿曼達是象徵性的運動世界的硬體。

sentences.english: Amanda must want to activate the stone dais as well.
sentences.chinese: 阿曼達也肯定很想親手觸發那個石祭臺。

sentences.english: Oman and Bahrain have free trade agreements with the United States.
sentences.chinese: 阿曼和巴林與美國簽訂了自由貿易協定。

sentences.english: We are using the term, Halls of Amenti, in two ways.
sentences.chinese: 我們以兩種格式操做“阿曼提除夜廳”阿誰術語。

sentences.english: To the Strait of Hormuz and the Gulf of Oman and the Arabian Sea converge.
sentences.chinese: 以霍爾木茲海峽和阿曼灣與阿拉伯海銜接。

sentences.english: Why did you do it, Armand?
sentences.chinese: 你爲什麼要這樣做，阿曼德？

sentences.english: Located in Oman peninsula west bank, in the Persian gulf coast.
sentences.chinese: 位於阿曼半島西岸，濱臨波斯灣。

sentences.english: There is, it was explained to us, a reason for such empathy.
sentences.chinese: 有人向我們解釋說，阿曼人的這種同情心是有道理的。

sentences.english: These last weeks, Devan has been planning to offer Amanda a job.
sentences.chinese: 最後幾周，德凡一直計劃給阿曼達安排一個工作。

sentences.english: Oman is the world"s easternmost Arabian country.
sentences.chinese: 阿曼是世界上最東面的阿拉伯國家。

sentences.english: The region of Oman was once known by its Sumerian name Magan.
sentences.chinese: 阿曼地區曾經因美根的閃族人而聞名。

sentences.english: Amanda Sharp, co-founder and director of Frieze thinks not.
sentences.chinese: 弗雷茲博覽會的創始人之一兼主任阿曼達？
